<subSubSection id="A4B6D4FDEFFCC6931F4FB88A32A69C73" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="5CC9AEA43E401E62C49369DA78FF8716" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3B34E97804686711D767EB41F3808611" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Honours Bob Drewes, the collector.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D7DEA0D362036B02B32B60B0000751B8" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="0AB23EBA1BF669B6ED0A80C5C175E02D" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4118BA91C6E72C38A4B84EA30153870C" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Distinguished from other species of the genus by the acuminate distal prolongation of the gonopod proplica. Post-torsal process of telopodite with two attached lamellae; apex rotated 360°ending in a tongue-shaped process.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1D38002DB7474CF5F074E2AC7BAF0F04" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" type="description">
<paragraph id="00760F9209416BE75BD83E197AAAD6F4" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="10FB57124B347B2F0371EAA723688B4C" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Holotype, adult male with 52 body rings (including preanal ring), length ca 65 mm (curved and broken), maximum body diameter 4.23 mm.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C042A28D5574EB9E713354D79A4C05BD" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Colour (in alcohol) predominantly brownish; prozonae yellowish brown; metazonae, legs, and antennae dark brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D6E7BBF6A27143C20030647630C2A086" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">
Head without modifications, smooth and polished, interantennal isthmus 1.11 mm, interocellarial isthmus 1.15 mm; antennae short (55% of maximum body diameter), extending up to posterior edge of collum; sensory pits on antennomeres 5 and 6 present, on 5th antennomere smaller. Eyes reniform, ommatidia arranged in five series: 9-8-7-6-4 = 34, counted from behind (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="904E827F0A959775382ED46622F0A7E6" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Globanus drewesi sp. nov., ♂ paratype. A habitus, lateral view B collum and segments 2 - 6, lateral view C frontal view of head D gnathochilarium E midbody transversal section F first pair of legs, oral view G second pair of legs, oral view H midbody legs, oral view I midbody claw, caudal view. Abbreviations: me = mentum, pe = penes, pfp = prefemoral process, s = seta at base of claw, sg = submedian transverse groove. Scale bars: 5 mm (A); 1 mm (B) 1 mm (D, E); 500 µm (C, D, F, G); 200 µm (H); 50 µm (I)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.930.49236.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/404816" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">2C</figureCitation>
). Gnathochilarium with a transverse row of about 10 setae along distal margin and 6 large setae on each lingual lamella; mentum elongate-triangular with a few setae and a well-marked submedian transverse groove (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="5EC6CEF61F67690444062FEE081F9B7D" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Globanus drewesi sp. nov., ♂ paratype. A habitus, lateral view B collum and segments 2 - 6, lateral view C frontal view of head D gnathochilarium E midbody transversal section F first pair of legs, oral view G second pair of legs, oral view H midbody legs, oral view I midbody claw, caudal view. Abbreviations: me = mentum, pe = penes, pfp = prefemoral process, s = seta at base of claw, sg = submedian transverse groove. Scale bars: 5 mm (A); 1 mm (B) 1 mm (D, E); 500 µm (C, D, F, G); 200 µm (H); 50 µm (I)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.930.49236.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/404816" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">2D</figureCitation>
, sg).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="874DF53C81C9B8695FED28F9FCB7A0A2" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">
Collum subcylindrical, smooth, lateral ends with three submarginal striae (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E21013E3775E6836DF033011B902DE01" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Globanus drewesi sp. nov., ♂ paratype. A habitus, lateral view B collum and segments 2 - 6, lateral view C frontal view of head D gnathochilarium E midbody transversal section F first pair of legs, oral view G second pair of legs, oral view H midbody legs, oral view I midbody claw, caudal view. Abbreviations: me = mentum, pe = penes, pfp = prefemoral process, s = seta at base of claw, sg = submedian transverse groove. Scale bars: 5 mm (A); 1 mm (B) 1 mm (D, E); 500 µm (C, D, F, G); 200 µm (H); 50 µm (I)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.930.49236.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/404816" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">2B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B353AC56B36FAB2331CCD3F93C367802" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">
Body rings circular (height/width ratio of midbody rings 0.98-1.0), no legless body rings in front of telson. Prozonae smooth, suture between pro- and metazonae straight. Metazonae equal in diameter to prozonae; metazonital striae present below ozopore level; ozopores starting with segment 6, rather vague, located just behind suture on midbody segments (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="BE5B2F2ABFE0E065297D743E6F6A8CCB" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Globanus drewesi sp. nov., ♂ paratype. A habitus, lateral view B collum and segments 2 - 6, lateral view C frontal view of head D gnathochilarium E midbody transversal section F first pair of legs, oral view G second pair of legs, oral view H midbody legs, oral view I midbody claw, caudal view. Abbreviations: me = mentum, pe = penes, pfp = prefemoral process, s = seta at base of claw, sg = submedian transverse groove. Scale bars: 5 mm (A); 1 mm (B) 1 mm (D, E); 500 µm (C, D, F, G); 200 µm (H); 50 µm (I)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.930.49236.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/404816" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">2B</figureCitation>
, oz). Paraprocts convex, distal margins set off by a submarginal groove. Hypoproct not fused to preceding segment.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6A7A4158B30720388E313F192871DDDE" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">
First pair of male Iegs as shown in Fig. 
<figureCitation id="107280A1E76DBD490075487340BFCCA3" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Globanus drewesi sp. nov., ♂ paratype. A habitus, lateral view B collum and segments 2 - 6, lateral view C frontal view of head D gnathochilarium E midbody transversal section F first pair of legs, oral view G second pair of legs, oral view H midbody legs, oral view I midbody claw, caudal view. Abbreviations: me = mentum, pe = penes, pfp = prefemoral process, s = seta at base of claw, sg = submedian transverse groove. Scale bars: 5 mm (A); 1 mm (B) 1 mm (D, E); 500 µm (C, D, F, G); 200 µm (H); 50 µm (I)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.930.49236.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/404816" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">2F</figureCitation>
, with 5 or 6 setose tubercles laterally; each prefemur with a prominent basal projection on anterior side and with short setae medially. Second pair of legs and penes as in Figure 
<figureCitation id="4CAB76523AE42AE108C5C50008E6EE6A" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Globanus drewesi sp. nov., ♂ paratype. A habitus, lateral view B collum and segments 2 - 6, lateral view C frontal view of head D gnathochilarium E midbody transversal section F first pair of legs, oral view G second pair of legs, oral view H midbody legs, oral view I midbody claw, caudal view. Abbreviations: me = mentum, pe = penes, pfp = prefemoral process, s = seta at base of claw, sg = submedian transverse groove. Scale bars: 5 mm (A); 1 mm (B) 1 mm (D, E); 500 µm (C, D, F, G); 200 µm (H); 50 µm (I)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.930.49236.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/404816" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">2E</figureCitation>
. Walking legs rather short (length 61% of midbody diameter, only tarsi visible from above when stretched; Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8110391CF2650B0F29E019A03D36C3AA" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Globanus drewesi sp. nov., ♂ paratype. A habitus, lateral view B collum and segments 2 - 6, lateral view C frontal view of head D gnathochilarium E midbody transversal section F first pair of legs, oral view G second pair of legs, oral view H midbody legs, oral view I midbody claw, caudal view. Abbreviations: me = mentum, pe = penes, pfp = prefemoral process, s = seta at base of claw, sg = submedian transverse groove. Scale bars: 5 mm (A); 1 mm (B) 1 mm (D, E); 500 µm (C, D, F, G); 200 µm (H); 50 µm (I)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.930.49236.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/404816" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">2E, H</figureCitation>
), distal third with ventral tibial pads extending to proximal third of tarsi. Tarsal claws long and curved, each with a small basal seta (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8786F7C2C09EA31DC5117C8FC49A0D85" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Globanus drewesi sp. nov., ♂ paratype. A habitus, lateral view B collum and segments 2 - 6, lateral view C frontal view of head D gnathochilarium E midbody transversal section F first pair of legs, oral view G second pair of legs, oral view H midbody legs, oral view I midbody claw, caudal view. Abbreviations: me = mentum, pe = penes, pfp = prefemoral process, s = seta at base of claw, sg = submedian transverse groove. Scale bars: 5 mm (A); 1 mm (B) 1 mm (D, E); 500 µm (C, D, F, G); 200 µm (H); 50 µm (I)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.930.49236.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/404816" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">2I, s</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F43E47D8953D981AA1D75B13EEC1D3E6" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">
Gonopods with a small sternum; proplica (pp) slender, with an acuminate distolateral spine and a field of short setae proximal to it. Metaplica (mp) slender proximally, expanded distally to form a latero-apical metaplical process (lap), slightly projecting outside the body when at rest (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2D779CC5CB44A04DF48193AD9B256DB7" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Globanus drewesi sp. nov. ♂ paratype. A, B left coxite, oral and caudal views, respectively C tip of left coxite, caudal view D, E left telopodite detached, anterior and posterior views, respectively F tip of left telopodite, posterior view. Abbreviations: atp = antetorsal process, bs = basomere, fb = flattened blade, lap = latero-apical process, map = meso-apical metaplical process, mp = metaplica, pp = proplica, ps = proplica spine, px = paracoxite, sp = subtriangular projection. Scale bars: 200 µm (A, B, D, E); 100 µm (C, F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.930.49236.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/404817" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">3A-C</figureCitation>
). Telopodite as shown in Figure 
<figureCitation id="0C54BCC204FDC9BCD1ADD9F6AE81C3FD" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Globanus drewesi sp. nov. ♂ paratype. A, B left coxite, oral and caudal views, respectively C tip of left coxite, caudal view D, E left telopodite detached, anterior and posterior views, respectively F tip of left telopodite, posterior view. Abbreviations: atp = antetorsal process, bs = basomere, fb = flattened blade, lap = latero-apical process, map = meso-apical metaplical process, mp = metaplica, pp = proplica, ps = proplica spine, px = paracoxite, sp = subtriangular projection. Scale bars: 200 µm (A, B, D, E); 100 µm (C, F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.930.49236.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/404817" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">3D, E</figureCitation>
, placed on anterior side of gonopod, antetorsal process (atp) long and slender, originating near arculus. Torsate region comprising less than half of telopodite length, distal third giving rise to a flattened blade (fb) and, beyond this, to a subtriangular projection (sp) (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B0E762A4845F114516C546B780C997E8" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Globanus drewesi sp. nov. ♂ paratype. A, B left coxite, oral and caudal views, respectively C tip of left coxite, caudal view D, E left telopodite detached, anterior and posterior views, respectively F tip of left telopodite, posterior view. Abbreviations: atp = antetorsal process, bs = basomere, fb = flattened blade, lap = latero-apical process, map = meso-apical metaplical process, mp = metaplica, pp = proplica, ps = proplica spine, px = paracoxite, sp = subtriangular projection. Scale bars: 200 µm (A, B, D, E); 100 µm (C, F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.930.49236.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/404817" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">3D</figureCitation>
). Apex rotated 360° ending in a tongue-shaped process. Prostatic groove running straight to tip of solenomere, ending just before the tongue-shape process level to a small digit (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B19E7C8416F748D9F1E02BE079BACB1E" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Globanus drewesi sp. nov. ♂ paratype. A, B left coxite, oral and caudal views, respectively C tip of left coxite, caudal view D, E left telopodite detached, anterior and posterior views, respectively F tip of left telopodite, posterior view. Abbreviations: atp = antetorsal process, bs = basomere, fb = flattened blade, lap = latero-apical process, map = meso-apical metaplical process, mp = metaplica, pp = proplica, ps = proplica spine, px = paracoxite, sp = subtriangular projection. Scale bars: 200 µm (A, B, D, E); 100 µm (C, F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.930.49236.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/404817" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">3F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D497A0B2BCA8B6D15DA0C173E68788C5" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Paratype male agrees with holotype in all structural details, but females larger (up to 80 mm in length and ca 6 mm in diameter), with short legs (ca 60% of midbody diameter) devoid of tibial pads; the number of body rings also varies between specimens (up to 56 body rings including preanal ring). Vulvae placed vertically inside segment 3; no setae on vulvae.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0FA9637408CA6B8A17FC257A2F4DB527" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">The other characters agree with those of the holotype.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A2173183DD9005A7D50F76A7F73D38DF" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="B930344E89A780ADB152863B5EB893FB" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="376A8E6B8084B4D830DEBB3C92C3A47B" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">
The species seems to be endemic to 
<normalizedToken id="AEB04BC5E03C63EEFFD6FBD3F5F04BE1" originalValue="São">Sao</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="613A03BF838600B8248FFAA1A79FA458" originalValue="Tomé">Tome</normalizedToken>
Island.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E3ACEFC3DDD662676BA046341192B30E" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" type="relationships">
<paragraph id="7CCB1A60A4FBFDAB609BB1EF900FA812" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Relationships.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EB8C71E53589F4A2CC9832F23897C21D" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">
Although the three species of 
<taxonomicName id="921272558FE57477F949C876A52E6C28" authorityName="Attems" authorityYear="1914" class="Diplopoda" family="Spirostreptidae" genus="Globanus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Globanus" order="Spirostreptida" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="13921924BE3ED1F24AF1D4A70F5F4693" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Globanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are externaly very similar, the gonopod structure suggests that the new species is closer to 
<taxonomicName id="49B48B9620BAE9FD7D6F68406869916A" genus="G." lsidName="G. marginescaber" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" rank="species" species="marginescaber">
<emphasis id="A5C8445BC35EBD926E6E733BB875CF95" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">G. marginescaber</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In both species, the median lamella of the telocoxite shows a well-marked distal proplica spine, which is absent in 
<taxonomicName id="C13B0D8F54EF0D54ACAC9CBB5C246CC4" genus="G." lsidName="G. integer" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" rank="species" species="integer">
<emphasis id="36F49B7F82BDF50E0B7E80ACBF215E75" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">G. integer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
